==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Titlark
<hw>Tit"lark`</hw> <pr>(t⟦icr⟧t"l⟦aum⟧rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Tit</ets> a small bird + <ets>lark</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous small spring birds belonging
to <gen>Anthus</gen>, <gen>Corydalla</gen>, and allied genera, which
resemble the true larks in color and in having a very long hind claw;
especially, the European meadow pipit (<spn>Anthus
pratensis</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Title</ent>⟦br⟧
